<h2>HVAC Systems in California</h2>
<h3>Climate Considerations</h3>
<p>California's diverse climate zones, ranging from Mediterranean coastal areas to hot desert regions and alpine conditions, require carefully tailored HVAC solutions. The California Energy Commission has established 16 distinct climate zones, each with specific energy efficiency requirements and recommended equipment specifications. Coastal Zone 3, encompassing much of the San Francisco Bay Area, requires minimal heating and moderate cooling, making heat pumps an ideal solution for year-round comfort with maximum energy efficiency.</p>

