<p>California's Title 24 energy efficiency standards mandate specific HVAC performance requirements, including minimum SEER ratings, proper sizing calculations, and duct sealing requirements. The regulations also promote heat pump technology in moderate climate zones and require smart thermostats in new construction. These standards ensure optimal system performance while reducing energy consumption and utility costs for homeowners.</p>

